social_posts.post_text: Announcing my new collection dropping on @niftygateway - Lost Luggage 🧳 This collection is a culmination of the digital art I’ve created over the last two years. I wanted these luggage pieces to explore concepts of time, space, and thought, some more literally than others. More details coming soon :) A big thanks to @dropandrender! #nft #digitalart #digitalartist #lostluggage #time #space #thought #trailer

Lost in Time.

At this moment, with the uncertainty of the world around us, we can sometimes feel a little lost. 

This collection is a culmination of the digital art I’ve created over the last two years. In previous collections, I’ve been drawn to using objects as vessels for revealing an inner, whimsical beauty. Luggage was a specific item I revisited in my work over the last couple of years. This was initially due to pandemic lockdowns and the fact that we were all restricted. Our suitcases were left unused and full of nothing but our hopes and dreams of traveling again in the future.

I wanted these luggage pieces to explore concepts of time, space, and thought, some more literally than others: when we’re trying to make sense of our thoughts in confusing times, when home feels so far away it may as well be on another planet, or when in different moments of our lives time has a peculiar way of passing at different speeds. Regardless of backgrounds and individual experiences I believe all of these situations are relatable and can cause people to feel lost.

Returning to the present moment, although the world has reopened its doors, we find ourselves in uncertain times. Impacted by many factors, including current market conditions and recent episodes in the Crypto and NFT industries, these feelings of uncertainty and lack of direction can resonate with a great deal of us. This collection acknowledges those emotions, but also represents the number of individuals still standing. Feeling lost is part of the growing pains we as a community must experience and doing so allows for the next steps in expanding and developing with the proper foundation.

Collectors who purchase all three editions will also receive ‘Totally Lost’, a remix of all three works in one long-form piece.

On December 14th I’ll be releasing a final piece in this collection via The Crypt Gallery called ‘Lost in the Crypt’. Collectors that buy a piece in this collection and own either 2 Gold or 1 Platinum ‘King of Midtown’ passes will get the piece for free. There will be other editions of ‘Lost in the Crypt’ available for purchase, price and editions TBD. 

A big shout out to @dropandrender!

Checks and Balances - an important in any system, and social media is no exception. Verification checks have been a way to confirm authenticity, but even that system is changing.

This is a giveaway piece for all of my current @makersplace collectors. You will need to claim via @manifoldxyz and have the chance to win a custom @infiniteobjects screen of the piece! More details coming in the nexty few days!

Couldn’t have rendered this in time without my friends at @dropandrender ! 

#social #loop #3d #cinema4d

Echo Chamber - Sharing content on social media can contribute to the echo chamber effect, where we only hear and see what we already agree with. It’s important to seek out diverse perspectives to break out of the echo chamber!

This piece will be available as an edition of 3 on @makersplace this Friday. Two will be fixed price with the option to buy a custom Infinite Objects screen, while one will be auctioned and come with a custom IO screen.

Thank you to @dropandrender for helping me get these pieces rendered! 

#satisfying #loop #3d #cinema4d

Reward Cycle - The social media reward cycle can make us feel like we need to constantly work for that dopamine hit. Always remember to take a step back and breath.

This piece will be available as an edition of 3 tomorrow on @makersplace. Two will be fixed price with the option to buy a custom Infinite Objects screen, while one will be auctioned and come with a custom IO screen!

Thank you to @dropandrender for helping me get these pieces rendered!

Antisocial, my latest collection now available on @makersplace 

‘Antisocial’ is a series of works that explore some of my thoughts on social media as an artist. To some extent we can all suffer from the grind of self-promotion and the pressure to maintain a curated persona. I’m not saying that I feel antisocial or am anti social media specifically, but highlighting the isolation or disconnection that can come with being constantly connected. Sometimes its good to get out there and touch the grass.

A look at the making of my work ‘Alotta Funny Money’ in memory of digital artist ‘Alotta Money’. It will be exhibited and auctioned to support Maggies Edinburgh at the @trevorjonesart #castleparty2023 with @makersplace in Paris this weekend!

In this tribute to Alotta, I've embraced fun chaos, touching on the irreverence and eccentricity so often found in his work. I built out the piece in C4D and rendered layers (thanks to @dropandrender ), pulling together in post. 

I put together a collection of six small animations to display on the monitors. From Alotta’s avatar to Bitcoin and the SEC. The bank note contains ‘092023’, as the auction & exhibit are in September.

The central Mandala has many streams of numbers emanating from the centre. These are all actually binary code for ‘Alotta Money’ 👀👀 The final artwork incorporates pastel hues and patterns reminiscent of European banknotes. 

Alotta’s four-eyed John Cleese inspired profile is keeping all his eyes on the markets, all at once - which are all over the place! I animated the avatar and cameras using deformers, fields and a lot of @greyscalegorilla signal tags! 

Thank you again to @trevorjonesart and @makersplace for inviting me to take part in this exhibit and auction. You can see and bid on all the artists works below, the auction starts at 10am EST Saturday! https://makersplace.com/exhibit/castle-party-2023-alotta-money-charity
Alotta Funny Money - my 1/1 tribute piece in memory of digital artist Alotta Money. The auction ends TODAY at 4.30pm BST / 11.30am EST!! I’ll add the auction link in my stories !
